description.narrative:
The GICHDs work is guided by the vision of a world in which communities thrive, free from explosive ordinance. To streamline its work towards this vision, the GICHD strategy 2019  2022 outlines a Theory of Change with immediate outcomes, intermediate outcomes and strategic objectives. Where the immediate outcomes are in the direct reach of the GICHD's work, the intermediate outcome relies on both meeting the immediate outcomes and factors beyond the GICHD's control. The four strategic objectives are high-level achievements which require collaborative efforts and positive results undertaken by a larger sphere of actors, stakeholders and donors supporting human security initiatives. They refer to the long-term improvement in society in terms of clearance, protection, sustainable development, equality and empowerment. These are believed to be achieved by enabling GICHD's partners to reduce risks to communities from explosive ordnance by furthering knowledge, promoting norms and standards, developing capacities, and facilitating dialogue and cooperation.

The strategic objectives are:
(1) Conventions are implemented, completion targets reached;
(2) Communities are protected from explosive harm;
(3) Land, housing and infrastructure are returned to communities, in support of sustainable livelihoods; and
(4) Gender Equality and inclusion are achieved and women and girls are empowered.
